Someone in the news gave some outrageous range that the sniper could be shooting from. I believe they said 600 or 700 yards. Making a shot from that distance is a miracle with a .223 round like the sniper is supposed to be using. A .50 caliber sniper rifle can make that kind of shot, but not a .223. At least, not any .223 rifle I know of can do that. A more realistic range is 100 to 200 yards. Within this range, a moderately skilled marksman with a decent weapon will hit his target almost every time. Three hundred yards is kind of pushing it. Anything more, and we'd probably be seeing more of a 25% or 50% kill rate instead of 80%<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just clearing some mis-information...<br>
<br>
An &quot;amazing&quot; shot with a .50 caliber sniper rifle (in competent hands) would be one in excess of 2000 meter. A 6-700 yard shot would be similar to throwing a rock and hitting the side of a tractor-trailer rig. On the note of the .223 being a poor performance bullet over long ranges...<br>
<br>
While working at Edson Range in Camp Pendleton, CA I got to take part in a little &quot;show&quot; that the local sharpshooters put on for some visiting high brass. These individuals put on full combat gear, including Alice pack, web gear, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> NBC protective headgear, and consistantly fired rounds into 1 1/2&quot; targets from 600 meters...with an unmodified M16A2 rifle. They were also doing this with the M14, and a few other weapons.<br>
<br>
A couple more examples of .22 caliber rounds used in extreme distance shooting:<br>
<br>
.220 Swift - Very, very fast round. Decently consistant.<br>
.22-250 - Very, very fast round. Very consistant under the right conditions.<br>
.222 (Hornet? Can't remember at the moment) Never used this round much.<br>
<br>
As to the sniper, I can't imagine what the people living there are going through. A few of my in-game friends live in the area, and one lives within walking distance of the gas station in one of the more recent shootings. Hopefully they'll find the bastard doing it before he ruins any more lives. <p>Blaesteil<br>
58 monk<br>
E'marr<br>
So that's what a <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84944" target="_blank">monkey</a> wears?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxphate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xphate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 7:25:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1680.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree with anarkhan</span><hr size=1> am I the only one who whants this guy alive?<br>
